  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency appeal COVID-19, Kabul and Herat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan is currently at high risk of being impacted by COVID-19, due to lack of public awareness (more than half the population is illiterate), lack of personal protective equipment, poverty, high number of individuals with chronic diseases, drug addition, high number of returnees from Iran. This project aims at preventing and controlling the spread of COVID-19 in Kabul and Herat, through increasing public awareness, training medical personnel and distributing personal protective equipment.</narrative>
  </description>
